decision_details:
- the proposal made by Hon. Salinda Dissanayake, 	Minister of Indigenous Medicine to repeal the existing Homeopathy Act which 	was enacted in 1970 and to present a new Bill for the purpose prepared by the 	Legal Draftsman, was approved by the Cabinet.  The new Bill will provide the 	following:

*	regulate and control the practice of Homeopathic medicine;

*	promote and encourage the study, research in and practice of Homeopathic medicine;

*	establish and maintain a Homeopathic Medical College;

*	develop or encourage measures for the investigation and treatment of diseases with a view to improve public health; and
		
*	regulate and control institutions providing treatment and control of the manufacture, importation, sale and distribution of Homeopathic drugs.
